  "id": "019ce9a0-2590-7392-9fb3-3644185c14c6",
  "content": "## Decision: Config-driven chat model registry for corvia-inference\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-13\n**Commits:** corvia `a836d86`, workspace `0b5d543`\n\n### Context\n\nThe chat model resolution in corvia-inference was hardcoded in a `resolve_model()` match block — adding or changing models required recompiling. The RAG `ask()` generation was disabled (no `[merge]` section in config).\n\n### Decision\n\n1. **Config-driven model registry**: Added `[inference.chat_models]` table to `corvia.toml` mapping short names (e.g. \"qwen3\") to HuggingFace repo + GGUF filename. The `ChatModelDef` struct lives in `corvia-common/config.rs` with serde defaults matching the hardcoded fallback.\n\n2. **Proto extension**: Added `hf_repo` (field 7) and `hf_filename` (field 8) to `LoadModelRequest` in `model.proto`. When set, the inference server skips internal `resolve_model()` and uses provided coordinates directly. Empty strings trigger the hardcoded fallback for backward compatibility.\n\n3. **Resolution flow**: CLI resolves model name → HF coordinates from config via `resolve_chat_model_coords()`, passes them through the provisioner (`ChatModelCoords` struct) to the inference server via gRPC. Warning printed when model name not found in registry.\n\n4. **ModelEntry stores HF coords**: The `ModelEntry` in `model_manager.rs` now persists `hf_repo`/`hf_filename` so `reload_models` can use config-provided coordinates for custom models not in the hardcoded fallback.\n\n5. **Default chat model: Qwen3 8B** (Q4_K_M, ~5GB from `bartowski/Qwen_Qwen3-8B-GGUF`). Selected based on benchmarks — top-ranked 8B model for instruction following and RAG grounded generation. Supports thinking/non-thinking modes. Apache 2.0 license.\n\n6. **GPU config**: Set `device = \"gpu\"`, `backend = \"cuda\"` in `[inference]` for NVIDIA GPU inference.\n\n### Sync requirement\n\n`resolve_model()` in `corvia-inference/src/chat_service.rs` and `default_chat_models()` in `corvia-common/src/config.rs` must stay in sync. Both have cross-reference comments. Long-term: remove hardcoded `resolve_model()` once config-driven resolution is proven stable.\n\n### Future: Dashboard model switching\n\nThe dashboard can change `[merge] model` via `corvia_config_set` hot-reload and add entries to `[inference.chat_models]` — no recompile needed.",
